ds can make patient transfer significantly easier.";i:35;s:165:"A bed transfer aid may assist in moving an individual from one side of the bed to the other sitting them up or moving them to or from bed from a chair or wheelchair.";i:36;s:91:"Essential Aids patient transfer equipment is all rigorously tested and the highest quality.";i:37;s:125:"Lifting your legs in and out of bed can often prove to be tricky especially if you lack muscle tone and strength in your leg.";i:38;s:129:"A recommended choice for this is to invest in a leg lifter aid which will help users move safely in and out of bed independently.";i:39;s:70:"For more information visit our dedicated Bedroom Disability Aids area.";i:40;s:107:"As well as steps a grab rail by the side of your bed can help you feel safe and secure once you are in bed.";i:41;s:73:"It can also give you something to hold onto as you get in and out of bed.";i:42;s:93:"The disabled steps you choose may also include grab rails to make them even safer and secure.";i:43;s:133:"If your bedroom is located on the upper floor of your home it can be tempting once again to spend a large amount of your time in bed.";i:44;s:138:"Join Licensed Physical Therapist Assistant Joshua Hancock as he shares a technique to help spine surgery patients get out of and into bed.";i:45;s:33:"Proximity to the Edge of the Bed.";i:46;s:74:"The first step is to bring the person in bed close to the edge of the bed.";i:47;s:82:"However make sure there is a safe distance between the person and edge of the bed.";i:48;s:19:"Roll onto the Side.";i:49;s:65:"Now that the patient is already close to the edge assist them in.";i:50;s:96:"To get the patient into a seated position roll the patient onto the same side as the wheelchair.";i:51;s:75:"Put one of your arms under the patients shoulders and one behind the knees.";i:52;s:113:"Swing the patients feet off the edge of the bed and use the momentum to help the patient into a sitting position.";i:53;s:40:"Move the patient to the edge of the bed.";i:54;s:63:"Standing aids provide support during the sit to stand transfer.";i:55;s:129:"If getting out of bed or out of a chair isnt as easy as it used to be then one of our standing aids may be all the help you need.";i:56;s:57:"There is a vast array of standing devices to choose from.";i:57;s:68:"With a little help from a standing aid standing becomes much easier.";i:58;s:89:"An accessible bedroom is one that is easy for disabled people to enter leave and live in.";i:59;s:210:"Making a room accessible involves complying to various guidelines and regulations in terms of structure layout design furniture and support all of which are there to ensure maximum possible comfort and ease of.";}}